    "long_instructions": "#### Predict\r\n\r\nThis program uses the <code style=\"background-color: rgb(242, 24, 162); color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">repeat</code> block with some of the blocks you've seen before. Before we run our code, let's write down some thoughts on what we think might happen.\r\n\r\n1) Write down anything you **notice** about the code. _It's okay to write things that feel obvious, like \"the new block is a different color\"_\r\n2) Make a **prediction** - what do you think will happen when you press Run? _This is just a guess - it's okay to be unsure!_\r\n\r\nOnce you've answered the questions, Press \"Run\" and listen. Then wait for next steps from your teacher.",
